name: ULTRAVATAR III - Ten Tickets to Paradise
description:
Ultravatar is dedicated to a special breed of beings - The virtual Character.
Once used by the Virtual-Industrial Complex (Game, Film and Advertising Industry) in every clips and trailers.
Here they are burned for every common product, with hundreds of their colleagues, as filler Material in "Massive Crowd Animations" for Hollywood blockbusters pushed to the end of the perceptible Image.
They end up dumped somewhere at the end of the Information Superhighway.
There I found them on the "Lost Highway" just before the "Titty Twister", battered and abused by a rigorous and unscrupulous Industry, that in pursuit of the ultimate and  perfect resolution, simply throws their children into the rubbish.

Massive Digital Assemblage 
JPEG 6900 x 6000 px
200 DPI
17021451 Polygons
Special Thanks to: Laurence Fuller and DIGX (Kopfgestaltung) for inspiring through REX
